<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1443,1759]" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1480,1506]" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">Remarks</emphasis>
. The above listed specimens are fully winged; four species belonging to this genus have tegmina longer than the abdomen: 
<taxonomicName authority="Uvarov, 1931" authorityName="Uvarov" authorityYear="1931" box="[450,715,1516,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="braini">
<emphasis box="[450,550,1516,1542]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. braini</emphasis>
Uvarov, 1931
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure, 1888" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1888" box="[728,1030,1516,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantans">
<emphasis box="[728,848,1517,1542]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. cantans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Saussure, H. de" box="[856,1030,1516,1542]" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref12777" refString="Saussure, H. de (1888) Addimenta ad Prodromum Oedipodiorum, Insectorum ex Ordine Orthopterorum. Memoires de la Societe de Physique et d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve, 30 (1), 1 - 180. [http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 50100  page / 71 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1888">Saussure, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure, 1884" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1884" box="[1043,1355,1516,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricatus">
<emphasis box="[1043,1176,1516,1542]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. loricatus</emphasis>
Saussure, 1884
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure, 1888" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. peringueyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Saussure, H. de" box="[277,449,1552,1578]" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref12777" refString="Saussure, H. de (1888) Addimenta ad Prodromum Oedipodiorum, Insectorum ex Ordine Orthopterorum. Memoires de la Societe de Physique et d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve, 30 (1), 1 - 180. [http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 50100  page / 71 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1888">Saussure, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. All occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[596,738,1552,1578]" name="South Africa" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and three (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uvarov" authorityYear="1931" box="[862,960,1552,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="braini">
<emphasis box="[862,960,1552,1578]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. braini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1888" box="[974,1092,1553,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantans">
<emphasis box="[974,1092,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. cantans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1888" box="[1145,1295,1553,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">
<emphasis box="[1145,1295,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. peringueyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the 
<collectingRegion country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">Cape province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[285,430,1588,1614]" name="South Africa" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. It is possible to exclude that the specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[969,1065,1588,1614]" name="Namibia" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">Namibia</collectingCountry>
is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uvarov" authorityYear="1931" box="[1096,1195,1588,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="braini">
<emphasis box="[1096,1195,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. braini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its very rugose integuments; following the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Saussure, H. de" box="[514,694,1624,1650]" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref12777" refString="Saussure, H. de (1888) Addimenta ad Prodromum Oedipodiorum, Insectorum ex Ordine Orthopterorum. Memoires de la Societe de Physique et d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve, 30 (1), 1 - 180. [http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 50100  page / 71 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1888">Saussure (1888)</bibRefCitation>
it was possible to exclude also 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1884" box="[1045,1176,1624,1650]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricatus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1176,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. loricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has brachypterous females. Sulphureous hind wings are typical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1888" box="[743,861,1661,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantans">
<emphasis box="[743,861,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. cantans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1888" box="[938,1090,1661,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">
<emphasis box="[938,1090,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. peringueyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has cerulean wings; Namibian specimens have sulphureous wings. Lüderitzbucht is ca. 
<quantity box="[790,876,1696,1722]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" unit="km" value="800.0">800 km</quantity>
from Prieska (the 
<typeStatus box="[1086,1134,1697,1723]" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1888" box="[1265,1383,1697,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Batrachotetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cantans">
<emphasis box="[1265,1383,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">B. cantans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); no fully winged species of this genus was hitherto known from 
<collectingCountry box="[828,928,1732,1758]" name="Namibia" pageId="20" pageNumber="49">Namibia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
